The paper deals with combinatorial auctions, which are a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of black-box access to a combinatorial auction algorithm and query access to sampled valuations suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of incentive compatibility and welfare maximization is a central theme in mechanism design (cs.EC). Finally, the use of Bayesian methods and probability distributions suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
